WEBVTT

00:08.269 --> 00:09.966
Previously
on "61st Street"...

00:10.097 --> 00:11.663
That's it.
That's the one.

00:11.794 --> 00:13.404
The prostate is enlarged.

00:13.535 --> 00:15.015
You okay?
Yeah.

00:15.145 --> 00:16.668
We could use your help
with this.

00:16.799 --> 00:18.627
13,000 cops
and they're not gonna be

00:18.757 --> 00:20.368
looking to take you
in alive.

00:20.498 --> 00:22.935
Defund the police!

00:23.066 --> 00:24.198
Bag and tag his clothes.

00:24.328 --> 00:26.330
Can you give me
some privacy?

00:26.461 --> 00:27.897
-How we lookin'?
-The house is all set.

00:28.028 --> 00:29.377
Cops don't know where he is.

00:29.507 --> 00:30.856
He needs to have his mother tell
him what to do.

00:30.987 --> 00:32.336
No! No!

00:32.467 --> 00:34.077
Moses!
Hey, don't shoot,
don't shoot.

00:34.208 --> 00:36.906
Run.Stop!
I'm this man's lawyer.

00:40.257 --> 00:42.520
Wait, where are
you taking him?

00:42.651 --> 00:44.696
Aye, man,
let me talk to my mom!

00:44.827 --> 00:45.523
Don't hurt him!

00:45.654 --> 00:46.959
Mama!

00:47.090 --> 00:48.657
Hey, let me talk to my mom,
man, please!

00:48.787 --> 00:51.703
Where are you
taking him?!

00:51.834 --> 00:52.965
Please!

00:53.096 --> 00:55.403
Let me talk to my mom.

00:57.231 --> 00:58.754
-Mo!

00:58.884 --> 01:00.060
-Aye, let me talk to her!
-Mo!

01:00.190 --> 01:02.627
Aye, Josh.
I ain't do anything, man!

01:02.758 --> 01:04.890
Why y'all gotta chain him
like that for, man?!

01:05.021 --> 01:07.328
-Okay, man, come on.
-Hold, hold up.
Hold, hold up, hold up.

01:07.458 --> 01:08.720
Don't you speak.
Not a word 'til I get there.

01:08.851 --> 01:09.852
I'm right behind you.
Do you hear me?

01:09.982 --> 01:11.332
Don't say a word!
Not a word!

01:11.462 --> 01:12.768
Mo!

01:12.898 --> 01:14.204
-Mama!
-It's okay, Mo!

01:16.163 --> 01:17.164
Thank you, Joshua.

01:18.861 --> 01:20.732
I got her.
I got her. I got her.

01:20.863 --> 01:22.256
I didn't even
do nothing, man!

01:22.386 --> 01:23.735
Aaargh!

01:23.866 --> 01:25.302
Alright, man, you got
this, aight, man?

01:25.433 --> 01:26.303
You gonna get out, aight?

01:26.434 --> 01:27.783
Aye, aye, Joshua!

01:27.913 --> 01:29.654
-You gonna get out!

01:29.785 --> 01:31.091
Man, y'all can't keep
doing this!

01:31.221 --> 01:34.094
Y'all can't keep doing
this shit, man!

01:36.270 --> 01:38.837
They can't keep fucking
doing this shit!

01:38.968 --> 01:40.404
You said
you're his lawyer.

01:40.535 --> 01:41.231
Yes.

01:41.362 --> 01:42.537
You be that.

01:42.667 --> 01:44.539
You be his lawyer.

01:44.669 --> 01:46.715
Mr. Franklin, please.

01:51.763 --> 01:53.287
Who made sergeant?

01:53.417 --> 01:54.940
Don't get bitter, Rossi.

01:55.071 --> 01:56.551
You won't get it
next time 'round, either,

01:56.681 --> 01:58.205
if you turn
into a bitter cop.

02:00.337 --> 02:03.123
You know,
my man in The Nation,

02:03.253 --> 02:04.428
he says all his people
are wondering

02:04.559 --> 02:06.517
why all the heat's on them,

02:06.648 --> 02:09.955
while The Faction get the
freedom of the South Side.

02:10.086 --> 02:12.132
That's just
what he tells me.

02:12.262 --> 02:13.611
And?

02:13.742 --> 02:15.352
Look...

02:15.483 --> 02:17.746
I don't care
who we take down.

02:17.876 --> 02:20.052
These people are
all the same to me.

02:20.183 --> 02:22.881
But they havegot to be
paying for that pass--

02:23.012 --> 02:24.579
The Faction.

02:24.709 --> 02:26.015
Paying who?

02:26.146 --> 02:27.495
It's just where
the heat is now.

02:29.627 --> 02:31.455
He got a name,

02:31.586 --> 02:33.109
your man in The Nation?

02:33.240 --> 02:34.371
Yeah.

02:34.502 --> 02:35.546
Tutu.

02:39.724 --> 02:42.727
But they havegot to be
paying for that pass--

02:42.858 --> 02:44.947
The Faction.

02:45.077 --> 02:45.817
Paying who?

03:06.708 --> 03:11.060
There's so much to love
about this town.

03:11.191 --> 03:13.018
Great food.

03:13.149 --> 03:16.196
Great teams.

03:16.326 --> 03:18.241
Great people.

03:18.372 --> 03:21.853
But you know what
I love the most?

03:21.984 --> 03:23.203
This damn lake.

03:25.640 --> 03:27.772
Always there

03:27.903 --> 03:30.732
and always different.

03:30.862 --> 03:31.994
Breaks my heart,
Michael Rossi

03:32.124 --> 03:35.258
will never see it again.

03:35.389 --> 03:36.520
You know how many
kids he had?

03:42.570 --> 03:43.310
Five.

03:47.749 --> 03:50.404
That has to be guilt.

03:50.534 --> 03:53.537
You were on the run,
but you had to know.

03:53.668 --> 03:54.408
Am I right?

03:57.454 --> 03:59.456
The thing about guilt --

03:59.587 --> 04:00.762
it comes from the gut.

04:02.677 --> 04:05.375
Like when you ran from us
on the corner.

04:05.506 --> 04:07.203
You weren't thinking.

04:07.334 --> 04:08.900
Your gut took over.

04:09.031 --> 04:10.337
When that happens,
you just do

04:10.467 --> 04:12.252
what your gut
tells you to do.

04:12.382 --> 04:15.342
My lawyer told me not
to talk to you.

04:15.472 --> 04:17.561
This ain't about lawyers.

04:17.692 --> 04:20.869
Judges, lawyers, they
don't buy the gut thing.

04:20.999 --> 04:22.871
They want reasons why.

04:23.001 --> 04:24.612
The gut's not in play
with those guys

04:24.742 --> 04:27.005
'cause they don't live
like we live.

04:27.136 --> 04:28.442
You and me, it's simple.

04:28.572 --> 04:30.879
You wanted to get away
from the cops, you ran.

04:31.009 --> 04:34.012
You wanted not to get caught
by a cop, you fought.

04:34.143 --> 04:36.363
That's all.

04:36.493 --> 04:38.974
The rest is just words.

04:39.104 --> 04:39.801
Right?

04:41.890 --> 04:42.586
Right.

04:48.636 --> 04:49.376
Okay.

05:01.562 --> 05:03.041
-Let's go!
-Aye.

05:09.831 --> 05:10.614
Unh!

06:04.364 --> 06:05.974
Shoelaces, belt.

06:37.484 --> 06:38.441
Come on, let's go.

06:51.976 --> 06:53.804
Give me 20 minutes
alone with him.

06:53.935 --> 06:56.328
Make sure it's not less.

06:56.459 --> 06:57.155
You got it.

07:11.300 --> 07:12.910
Your call has been forwarded.

07:27.664 --> 07:29.057
Get down here, now.

07:42.287 --> 07:43.898
I want to apologize.

07:47.336 --> 07:50.992
It got a little
aggressive back there.

07:51.122 --> 07:52.602
We lost one of our guys.

07:54.343 --> 07:57.564
Emotions run high.

07:59.566 --> 08:00.436
Please.

08:08.052 --> 08:11.795
I just got off the phone
with your coach, Angelo.

08:11.926 --> 08:16.321
Before that, I spoke
to your history teacher.

08:16.452 --> 08:18.106
Both full respect,

08:18.236 --> 08:20.891
for you
and who you are.

08:23.154 --> 08:25.200
I --

08:25.330 --> 08:26.941
I-I--

08:27.071 --> 08:28.333
I didn't do anything.
I didn't -- I didn't --

08:28.464 --> 08:30.074
I didn't
do anything.

08:30.205 --> 08:33.034
I've looked in the eyes
of some very bad people.

08:35.645 --> 08:38.430
And I feel like I can see
a man's soul in his eyes.

08:40.476 --> 08:43.740
I look at you,

08:43.871 --> 08:47.527
I see a good kid
who's been shaken up

08:47.657 --> 08:49.529
and needs a little help
settling down again.

08:53.271 --> 08:54.664
Moses, do you know what

08:54.795 --> 08:58.189
a memorandum
of cooperation is?

08:58.320 --> 09:01.976
It's an agreed version
of the truth.

09:02.106 --> 09:04.239
We agree on the truth.

09:04.369 --> 09:07.111
We cooperate
with each other.

09:07.242 --> 09:08.765
You get to go home
where you belong.

09:12.377 --> 09:14.205
So I wrote up
what we said in the car.

09:19.297 --> 09:22.823
"I knew they were police
and my gut said run,

09:22.953 --> 09:25.129
so I ran."

09:25.260 --> 09:26.043
That fair?

09:29.220 --> 09:31.919
"The cop chasing me had me
down a dead-end street."

09:33.660 --> 09:35.357
Blackstone
or South Blackstone?

09:42.886 --> 09:44.235
Blackstone.

09:44.366 --> 09:45.149
Thank you.

09:47.674 --> 09:49.589
Um...

09:49.719 --> 09:50.807
"I had to get away."

09:53.157 --> 09:55.333
"I made a move
toward the cop"?

09:55.464 --> 09:57.248
"I ran toward the cop"?
-I didn't -- that.

09:57.379 --> 09:58.815
I didn't do that.
I didn't intend for that.

09:58.946 --> 10:02.993
Maybe, maybe we do a little
lawyer language here.

10:03.124 --> 10:04.386
Sometimes easier.

10:04.516 --> 10:07.432
So that would be...

10:07.563 --> 10:13.395
"Pursuant to my attempt
to escape,

10:13.525 --> 10:15.702
there was physical contact...

10:17.747 --> 10:23.405
...between myself
and the police officer,

10:23.535 --> 10:25.363
as a consequence of which...

10:27.496 --> 10:28.497
...he hit his head."

10:31.065 --> 10:32.762
That didn't happen.
It didn't --

10:32.893 --> 10:34.155
I didn't intend
for that to happen

10:34.285 --> 10:35.460
because he was running
and I was trying

10:35.591 --> 10:36.897
to run at the side

10:37.027 --> 10:38.594
and I was trying --
-This is just you, me,

10:38.725 --> 10:40.727
and the facts.

10:40.857 --> 10:42.380
So, so, so,

10:42.511 --> 10:44.992
so what if I don't want
to do this memorandum?

10:45.122 --> 10:46.602
What if I
don't cooperate?

10:50.693 --> 10:52.173
Then, it'll be other cops.

10:53.783 --> 10:55.306
With all their anger

10:55.437 --> 10:57.134
about what happened
to one of their guys.

10:58.788 --> 11:01.748
If I can't show my people
proof of your cooperation,

11:01.878 --> 11:03.097
they pull me out

11:03.227 --> 11:05.665
and they pull in your mom
and Joshua

11:05.795 --> 11:08.406
and your buddy Marquise,

11:08.537 --> 11:09.930
on account of the pressure
they're under.

11:11.888 --> 11:13.281
But none of that happens

11:13.411 --> 11:15.065
if I show them
our memorandum.

11:16.110 --> 11:17.067
You sign this...

11:20.941 --> 11:22.290
...and everybody
stands down.

11:26.468 --> 11:27.948
I'll give you a minute
to think about it.

11:33.301 --> 11:34.911
Think about your
responsibilities.

11:51.841 --> 11:53.843
Aah!

12:11.208 --> 12:12.601
Sir, if you don't
fill out the form --

12:12.732 --> 12:14.255
You know who I am and you
know who I'm here to see.

12:14.385 --> 12:15.299
I'm not filling out
any form.

12:17.737 --> 12:20.130
You don't fill out the form,
you don't see your client.

12:20.261 --> 12:21.828
You're stalling me.
Please stop stalling me.

12:21.958 --> 12:23.264
Let me see my client,
please.

12:23.394 --> 12:24.482
Mr. Johnson is ready

12:24.613 --> 12:25.440
to see his lawyer.
-Thank you.

12:37.452 --> 12:38.148
We got him.

12:40.498 --> 12:43.153
What's he saying?

12:43.284 --> 12:44.285
We got that, too.

12:52.815 --> 12:55.122
What was the very last
thing I said?

12:55.252 --> 12:56.558
We just talked about what
happened in the car.

12:56.688 --> 12:58.647
-Moses, Moses!
-He sounded like he

12:58.778 --> 12:59.953
was trying to help me.
-Help you?!

13:00.083 --> 13:00.910
Yeah, that's
what it felt like!

13:01.041 --> 13:02.520
And now?

13:02.651 --> 13:04.261
How does it feel now?

13:07.874 --> 13:09.789
I don't feel guilty.

13:09.919 --> 13:11.399
I don't feel like I'm
a murderer or nothing.

13:11.529 --> 13:13.270
That piece of paper
you signed,

13:13.401 --> 13:14.968
in the eyes of the law,

13:15.098 --> 13:16.796
it says you're both.

13:22.671 --> 13:24.325
Law ain't right,
Mr. Franklin.

13:27.894 --> 13:28.938
The law ain't right.

13:35.902 --> 13:37.904
What'd you do to him?!

13:38.034 --> 13:38.774
Excuse me?

13:38.905 --> 13:39.862
You heard me.

13:39.993 --> 13:41.037
Officer Young.

13:42.996 --> 13:46.086
Can you help my lawyer
friend out here?

13:46.216 --> 13:48.610
Anything happen in the car
on the way to the station?

13:48.740 --> 13:49.654
Anything
you didn't like?

13:51.178 --> 13:52.919
Nope.

13:53.049 --> 13:53.963
So maybe it's you.

13:54.094 --> 13:54.834
What?

13:54.964 --> 13:56.009
Playing the race card.

13:56.139 --> 13:57.445
It's up the sleeve
of every

13:57.575 --> 13:58.881
liberal lawyer
in America right now.

13:59.012 --> 14:01.057
I see you, Brannigan.

14:01.188 --> 14:02.754
I know what you are.

14:02.885 --> 14:04.974
I've been seeing you
for the last 30 years,

14:05.105 --> 14:06.149
doing what I do.

14:06.280 --> 14:07.542
And Isee you.

14:07.672 --> 14:09.152
You're at the end
of your career

14:09.283 --> 14:10.632
and looking to go out
with a bang.

14:10.762 --> 14:11.938
You know your problem?

14:12.068 --> 14:14.288
Square peg, round hole.

14:14.418 --> 14:15.985
I'm just not
what you want me to be.

14:16.116 --> 14:18.422
I got to admit
I was surprised.

14:18.553 --> 14:20.381
Never had you down
as an ambulance chaser.

14:20.511 --> 14:21.512
Oh, yeah?

14:21.643 --> 14:22.687
Well, if it's not that,

14:22.818 --> 14:23.906
then how did you know

14:24.037 --> 14:25.473
where the most wanted
murder suspect

14:25.603 --> 14:26.822
in the history
of this city

14:26.953 --> 14:29.651
was hiding out,
and we didn't, hmm?

14:29.781 --> 14:31.914
What were you going
to do, Franklin,

14:32.045 --> 14:33.829
put him in the trunk
and head down to Mexico?

14:33.960 --> 14:35.091
You don't scare me,
Brannigan.

14:36.440 --> 14:38.486
Then you can leave.

14:38.616 --> 14:41.054
Or you can stay.

14:41.184 --> 14:42.533
But, if you stay,

14:42.664 --> 14:45.145
it's going to be on a charge
of obstructing justice

14:45.275 --> 14:46.842
and aiding and abetting
a fugitive.

14:59.028 --> 15:00.595
Hey, baby.

15:00.725 --> 15:02.510
The doctor called me.
What-What's going on,

15:02.640 --> 15:03.903
Franklin?
-It-It's -- It's nothing.

15:04.033 --> 15:05.078
Why does Dr. Algren need

15:05.208 --> 15:06.644
to speak to you so badly,

15:06.775 --> 15:08.820
he calls me three times?
-I missed an appointment.

15:08.951 --> 15:09.909
They hate it
when that happens.

15:10.039 --> 15:11.475
Is it your knee again?

15:11.606 --> 15:12.999
Oh, you got to be
kidding me.

15:13.129 --> 15:14.435
-Franklin.
-You got to be kidding.

15:14.565 --> 15:15.871
-What is it?
-I-I-I got to go.

15:16.002 --> 15:16.785
I-I'll see you tonight.
I love you.

15:16.916 --> 15:17.786
Franklin.

15:29.058 --> 15:30.712
-Jack.
-Are you kidding me?

15:30.842 --> 15:32.018
-Jack.
-A big murder

15:32.148 --> 15:33.323
five minutes
before you retire?

15:33.454 --> 15:34.672
I don't think so.
-Who gets it, Jack?

15:34.803 --> 15:35.804
-Not you.
-Yes, but who?

15:35.935 --> 15:37.458
-Danny Pascoe.
-Danny Pascoe --

15:37.588 --> 15:40.069
conveyor belt lawyer.

15:40.200 --> 15:41.244
I want this, Jack.

15:41.375 --> 15:43.203
You can't have it.

15:43.333 --> 15:46.032
Then it's over.

15:46.162 --> 15:47.990
What?

15:48.121 --> 15:49.861
If you won't let me
represent Moses Johnson

15:49.992 --> 15:53.126
as a public defender,
you give me no choice.

15:53.256 --> 15:53.953
What are you
talking about?

15:54.083 --> 15:55.867
I'm resigning, Jack,

15:55.998 --> 15:58.087
and I'm going to represent
him privately.

15:58.218 --> 15:59.959
This is crazy.

16:00.089 --> 16:02.962
Sometimes community
is the same as family,

16:03.092 --> 16:04.354
and that's where I am
with Moses.

16:04.485 --> 16:06.966
And, when it's family,
you don't say no.

16:07.096 --> 16:08.097
You step in.

16:08.228 --> 16:09.969
And nobody,
not even the man

16:10.099 --> 16:12.928
I trust most
in this whole building,

16:13.059 --> 16:15.148
is going to get in my way.

16:20.762 --> 16:22.851
Well, at least they're
paying attention.

16:22.982 --> 16:25.071
Maybe tone it down
a little?

16:28.857 --> 16:30.032
Oh, is that the reporter?

16:30.163 --> 16:31.077
Mm-hmm.

16:32.687 --> 16:33.557
Bet.

16:36.125 --> 16:37.561
Good afternoon!

16:37.692 --> 16:38.954
Good afternoon.

16:39.085 --> 16:40.912
Thank y'all for coming.

16:41.043 --> 16:44.568
So, there's a reporter here,
third row.

16:44.699 --> 16:46.309
We have Mr. Sessions, right?

16:46.440 --> 16:47.571
Peter Sessions.

16:47.702 --> 16:49.182
Yeah.

16:49.312 --> 16:52.446
Mr. Sessions is saying
that I am

16:52.576 --> 16:54.317
"barefoot and dangerous."

16:54.448 --> 16:55.710
-Mm.
-Ha!
-Dead right.

16:55.840 --> 16:56.972
No, it's alright. He's right.

16:57.103 --> 16:59.279
I amdangerous.

16:59.409 --> 17:04.414
Women have always been judged
in this way.

17:04.545 --> 17:07.287
Jeannette Rankin ran
for Congress in 1916

17:07.417 --> 17:10.507
and they said that her gowns
were too "severe."

17:10.638 --> 17:12.640
Hillary Clinton --
they said that she was

17:12.770 --> 17:14.816
"confused about her gender"

17:14.946 --> 17:17.471
because her pantsuits
were too baggy.

17:17.601 --> 17:19.560
After all of this time,

17:19.690 --> 17:21.083
they are still more comfortable

17:21.214 --> 17:24.478
with women carrying babies
than ballots.

17:24.608 --> 17:26.610
Come on, now.
-And here I come,

17:26.741 --> 17:29.135
shoeless, barefoot me,

17:29.265 --> 17:33.008
and he is more concerned
about what is not on my feet

17:33.139 --> 17:34.792
than what is coming
out of my mouth.

17:34.923 --> 17:36.707
Say that.

17:36.838 --> 17:38.361
So we have to ask ourselves,

17:38.492 --> 17:42.235
what is -- is hiding
underneath the cheap headline?

17:43.932 --> 17:45.716
I know.

17:45.847 --> 17:48.763
Everywoman
in this room knows.
Right.

17:48.893 --> 17:51.983
- Right.
- It's fear.

17:52.114 --> 17:56.162
It's fear because I am
demanding accountability

17:56.292 --> 17:58.164
from the
Chicago Police Department.

17:58.294 --> 17:59.556
- Say that!
- Right!

17:59.687 --> 18:01.950
Fear that I want to end policing

18:02.081 --> 18:05.693
that's just personal security
for rich white folks.

18:05.823 --> 18:08.826
Tell 'em, tell 'em.
-Fear that I am demanding an end

18:08.957 --> 18:12.308
to the executions of Black
and brown children.

18:12.439 --> 18:14.789
Fear I want to build a movement.

18:14.919 --> 18:17.313
I want to build a future
where Black and brown children

18:17.444 --> 18:18.967
can bechildren

18:19.098 --> 18:21.491
and where they are safe
and where they can thrive.

18:21.622 --> 18:25.495
And Mr. Sessions here is afraid
because, in that future,

18:25.626 --> 18:27.889
he has to lose
his first place in line.

18:28.019 --> 18:30.326
It ain't about my shoes!

18:30.457 --> 18:32.502
It ain't
about my shoes.

18:32.633 --> 18:34.200
Don't get distracted!

18:34.330 --> 18:36.027
